h examining our actions—maybe it existed from the start. \\n\\nI wonder if using a system property provider is the right choice. Instead, should I consider testImplementation with `org.glassfish:jakarta.el`? Also, creating fake replacements for API types in their real packages could be a potential issue, but we haven’t put anything in the real package, so does that make it acceptable?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing API dependencies**\\n\\nThe target artifact is API-only, which means the standalone behavior of ELProcessor requires an ExpressionFactory implementation. The default fallback is `com.sun.el.ExpressionFactoryImpl`. \\n\\nFor the test dependency, I think `org.glassfish:jakarta.el` is the right choice. However, I wonder if the EL 5 implementation might be `org.glassfish.expressly:expressly:5.0.0` instead, with `org.glassfish:jakarta.el` being an older version. \\n\\nAdding a testRuntimeOnly dependency could be fine. Considering the existing pattern with `ELUtil`, there’s potential for acceptance despite using `TestExpressionFactory` indirectly. But should I avoid dynamic access with `ExpressionFactory.newInstance`? I’m not so sure.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring ELManager options**\\n\\nI'm considering how to set `ELManager.exprFactory`, but reflection is prohibited. Maybe I could use `ELManager.setELContext(custom ELContext)` to map functions into a custom context, thus avoiding the ExpressionFactory issue. However, I realize that the ELProcessor constructor has already initialized the factory, which complicates things. \\n\\nI think it's best not to pursue this further, as it seems like there won't be a straightforward solution to manipulate the factory at this stage.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added a dedicated active-class test file:\n\n- `tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/ELProcessorTest.java`\n\nCoverage added for `jakarta.el.ELProcessor#defineFunction` paths:\n\n- Class loading via `Class.forName(...)`\n- Name-only method mapping via `getDeclaredMethods()`\n- Signature-based method mapping via `getDeclaredMethod(...)`\n- Parameter type resolution through `toClass(...)`\n- Reference class loading via `ClassLoader#loadClass(...)`\n- One-dimensional array class construction via `Array.newInstance(Class, int)`\n- Multi-dimensional array class construction via `Array.newInstance(Class, int[])`\n\nI did not run the tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01be2842630e2bf3016a272d27125481949787d8cacc4a2154\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 497, "output": 817, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34594, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780952343625, "responseId": "resp_01be2842630e2bf3016a272d181a748194bd564601dc703366"}, "toolResults": []}
